metadata.name: Stoplight - 16th and Locust
metadata.description: This image is part of an ongoing series exploring urban utility poles as sculptural objects. This visual is composed of three different photographs. The foreground is an intersection in Philadelphia at the corner of 16th and Locust st. The midground wall to the left of the composition is the street wall of Municipal Plaza in Philadelphia on JFK Blvd, and the background image is the skyline of New Orleans.
